---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <main style="max-width: 700px; margin: 2rem auto; padding: 2rem; background: #fff; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 2px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);">
    <h1 style="font-size: 2.2rem; color: #2d3748; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Documentation Guidelines</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #4a5568;">This documentation follows the rules and guidelines of the Certo repository. Please read and respect the following:</p>
    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem; color: #2b6cb0;">Code of Conduct</h2>
    <ul style="font-size: 1.05rem; color: #374151; padding-left: 1.5rem;">
      <li>Be respectful and considerate in all interactions.</li>
      <li>Use welcoming and inclusive language.</li>
      <li>Avoid demeaning, discriminatory, or harassing behavior and speech.</li>
      <li>See the <a href="https://github.com/Schroedinger-Hat/certo/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md" style="color: #3182ce; text-decoration: underline;" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Code of Conduct</a> for full details.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem; color: #2b6cb0;">Contributing to Documentation</h2>
    <ul style="font-size: 1.05rem; color: #374151; padding-left: 1.5rem;">
      <li>Follow the <a href="https://github.com/Schroedinger-Hat/certo/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md" style="color: #3182ce; text-decoration: underline;" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contributing Guide</a> for reporting issues, proposing changes, and submitting pull requests.</li>
      <li>Use clear, imperative commit messages (prefer Conventional Commits).</li>
      <li>Keep documentation changes focused and atomic.</li>
      <li>Add or update documentation tests/examples where applicable.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem; color: #2b6cb0;">Structure & Best Practices</h2>
    <ul style="font-size: 1.05rem; color: #374151; padding-left: 1.5rem;">
      <li>Organize documentation in logical sections and use clear headings.</li>
      <li>Provide examples, code snippets, and screenshots where helpful.</li>
      <li>Link to relevant API docs, guides, and external resources.</li>
      <li>Keep documentation up to date with code changes.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem; color: #2b6cb0;">License</h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; color: #374151;">By contributing to documentation, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the project's license. See the <a href="https://github.com/Schroedinger-Hat/certo/blob/main/LICENSE" style="color: #3182ce; text-decoration: underline;" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LICENSE</a> file for details.</p>
    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem; color: #2b6cb0;">Thank You</h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; color: #38a169;">We appreciate every contribution, from bug reports to documentation fixes. If you want help getting started, comment on an issue or open a discussion and we'll point you to a good first task.</p>
  </main>
</Layout>
